==English==
{{wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
From {{w|international scientific vocabulary}}, from {{uder|en|fr|xanthine}}, reflecting New Latin {{w|classical compound|combining forms}}: {{confix|en|xanth|ine}}; ultimately from {{uder|en|grc|ξανθός||yellow}}, because xanthine is yellowish-white.
===Pronunciation===
* {{homophones|en|xanthein|xanthene}}
===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# {{lb|en|chemistry}} Any of a group of [[alkaloid]]s that include [[caffeine]], [[theophylline]], and [[theobromine]] as well as the [[parent compound]], a precursor of [[uric acid]] found in many organs of the body.
====Usage notes====
* There is much confusion between this word and {{m|en|xanthein}}, and they are often interchanged.
====Derived terms====
* {{l|en|methylxanthine}}
* {{l|en|nonxanthine}}
* {{l|en|xanthine oxidase}}
* {{l|en|zooxanthine}}
